{"name": "pyspeedtest", "metadata": {"name": "pyspeedtest", "version": "1.2.7", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.0", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.1", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5"], "home_page": "https://github.com/fopina/pyspeedtest", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Speedtest.net Python script", "upload_time": 1470475400}, "documentation": ["# pyspeedtest\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.org/fopina/pyspeedtest.svg?branch=master\n:alt: Build Status\n:target: https://travis-ci.org/fopina/pyspeedtest\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pyspeedtest.svg\n:alt: PyPI Version\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyspeedtest\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/pyspeedtest.svg\n:alt: PyPI Python Versions\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyspeedtest\n```\n\nPython script to test network bandwidth using Speedtest.net servers\n\n## Installation\n\nThis package is available from PyPI so you can easily install it with:\n\n```bash\nsudo pip install pyspeedtest\n```\n\nOr only for your user\n\n```bash\n$ pip install --user pyspeedtest\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nIn a terminal:\n\n```bash\n$ pyspeedtest -h\nusage: pyspeedtest [OPTION]...\n\nTest your bandwidth speed using Speedtest.net servers.\n\noptional arguments:\n  -d L, --debug L   set http connection debug level (default is 0)\n  -m M, --mode M    test mode: 1 - download\n                               2 - upload\n                               4 - ping\n                               1 + 2 + 4 = 7 - all (default)\n  -r N, --runs N    use N runs (default is 2)\n  -s H, --server H  use specific server\n  -v, --verbose     output additional information\n  --version         show program's version number and exit\n```\n\n```bash\n$ pyspeedtest\nUsing server: speedtest.serv.pt\nPing: 9 ms\nDownload speed: 148.17 Mbps\nUpload speed: 18.56 Mbps\n```\n\nFrom a python script:\n\n```python\n>>> import pyspeedtest\n>>> st = pyspeedtest.SpeedTest()\n>>> st.ping()\n9.306252002716064\n>>> st.download()\n42762976.92544772\n>>> st.upload()\n19425388.307319913\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.README", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyspeedtest", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "pyspeedtest.content", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "length", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return alphanumeric string of indicated length."]}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.init_logging", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "loglevel", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Initialize program logger."]}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.parseargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.perform_speedtest", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "opts", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.pretty_speed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "speed", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyspeedtest.randint", "asynchronous": false, "params": [